reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on August 12, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Amazing... Turned out better than expected!
reviews.reviewText: I gotta say what an amazing product. I have a Lancool 2 Mesh case and decided to take off front panel to replace with these filters. (The case's front panel is already mesh but the holes are 1.5mm compared to this 0.8mm, and my pc was gettin more dust than I wanted). This was so easy to do. Unroll the mesh, measure, mark with pencil, and cut. Any scissors will do, that's how ez it was. Magnets stick nicely, mesh didnt fall. I did filters for front panel and also top (see pics), and still got like 1/4 of the mesh leftover. As for quality, these mesh are solid, stiff (while still being ez enuff to be cut with scissors). Dont worry about your front intake fans sucking them and makin them flimsy. Definitely recommend!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 18, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Working great for me with a Phanteks p500A
reviews.reviewText: This kit was a breeze to size and put together, and it's working great. The Phanteks p500a has a bit of an unusual front mesh panel, with machined angles that require some attention to detail to make a filter for, but it wasn't hard to do with the included materials and after making my filter I have enough material left over to make another one if the need arises. When I look at how much it would have cost to buy a pre-made product for this purpose, it would have been over $30 shipped, and even then I would have still worried about it not providing enough coverage for the angled air intake parts of the front panel (what good is a filter if it only blocks right in front of the fans - better than nothing, but it has to be over all of the possible intake area to stop dust getting in!). With this kit I was able to size it to fit and get it working in less than 20 minutes, and it is filtering really well.Great product, I recommend it!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 24, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great for when you need to make your OWN dust covers.
reviews.reviewText: Worked very well when I needed to make a triple 140 dust cover on the front of my case. Easy to cut, and easy to apply the magnet strips that are included. My ONLY gripe, is the way it is shipped. Comes in a tube with the mesh rolled up inside. It is a complete pain to work with to unroll to get it to lay flat. This was fixed by unrolling it, laying it flat and putting some heavy flat books on it to get it to lay flat. Once flat, SIMPLE to measure up, cut and add the magnetic strips! Doesnt seem to hinder the air flow much as under load temps didnt change at all with or without the mesh. Would recommend if you need to make your own dust covers!

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars It's good, no crease, good magnets.
reviews.reviewText: The mesh rolled out easily without any creases. The magnetic strips adhered to the mesh very well and they were also easy to cut with just a scissors. It has been holding up well.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 11, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Nice screen/mesh but terrible magnetic strio
reviews.reviewText: I cut the mesh screen and applied the doubled sided magnetic tape, but unfortunately it doesn't stick to my case well. I flattened out the rolled up mesh for a day, but it didn't help at all. I even tried gluing small magnets to the tape but that also did not help
Doing some mods, and this ended up being a perfect match for the mesh on my Corsair 110R case. I curled the mesh the opposite way and put it back in the packaging for a while to help flatten it out.
Only came with the magnetic tape, mesh is nowhere to be found
Perfect size for what I needed and easy to do

I used this product to replace the front glass on my deep cool matrix 55 because I wanted more airflow, the product decently does the job easy to cut to shape with a little assistance from another pair of hands, does tend to want to curl back on its self a lot.That being said it will not lay completely flat. Very close but bubbles are noticeable with leaving air gaps between tape and the case. Works but isn't perfect 4/10

The material is not all that great or sturdy, which means durability is significantly impacted as a result. The installation is a pain and the magnets included aren't anywhere near strong enough to hold down the mesh material; it just doesn't work no matter how hard you try. You'll have to apply more magnetic tape and possibly even use real glue/tape to hold it down. I'd save my time look for another product that actually works well.
